description: Data is considered categorical if it can only take a limited set of different values.

description: The logical Data type detected by Collibra profiling.

description: The number of empty values for that column

name: Maximum Text Length
description: The length of the longest text value in this column

name: Maximum Value
description: The maximum value, using alphabetical order for text

name: Mean
description: The mean of values (numeric only), excluding missing values

name: Median
description: The data median value

description: The length of the shortest text value in this column

description: The minimum value, using alphabetical order for text

name: Mode
description: The value with the highest frequency for a categorical feature.

name: Number of distinct values
description: The number of different values stored in this column

name: Number of Times Requested
description: The number of times this asset has been requested for permissible use.

name: Number of Times Viewed
description: Number of times this asset has been viewed.   This value needs to be updated using a workflow.

name: Personally Identifiable Information
description: An indicator to flag an asset that could potentially be used to identify a specific individual.

name: Profiled Row Count
description: The number of rows from the data set that were selected for profiling

description: The statistical standard deviation of values (numeric only)
